cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DS 

This paper deals with information theory, networking, and queueing theory, which are all covered by the arXiv categories cs.IT, cs.NI, and cs.SY. The paper also discusses the use of random linear coding, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM), and the characterization of stable throughput, which is related to data structures (cs.DS).
